WEBVTT

00:00:02.900 --> 00:00:05.967
[SINGING IN JAPANESE]

00:01:31.233 --> 00:01:34.166
RUKIA:
So tomorrow, I die.

00:01:34.166 --> 00:01:36.767
It seems strange,
but even when I heard

00:01:36.767 --> 00:01:40.200
that my execution
was set for tomorrow,

00:01:40.200 --> 00:01:42.400
I wasn't sad.

00:01:44.200 --> 00:01:47.934
It must because of
the dream I had last night.

00:01:47.934 --> 00:01:49.200
That dream...

00:01:49.200 --> 00:01:53.000
about the night
I can never forget.

00:01:57.200 --> 00:01:59.100
MAN:
Please, wait in
here for a moment.

00:01:59.100 --> 00:02:00.967
The lieutenant will
be here shortly.

00:02:00.967 --> 00:02:02.533
Make yourself comfortable.

00:02:02.533 --> 00:02:03.734
I, um--

00:02:03.734 --> 00:02:05.867
Yes, what is it?

00:02:05.867 --> 00:02:08.500
I'm just an ordinary
new member in the squad.

00:02:08.500 --> 00:02:11.500
Please try to treat be
the same as everyone else here.

00:02:11.500 --> 00:02:13.133
Oh, yes. Of course.

00:02:13.133 --> 00:02:14.266
I'll try to keep it in mind.

00:02:14.266 --> 00:02:15.533
[LAUGHS]

00:02:15.533 --> 00:02:16.834
[SIGHS]

00:02:16.834 --> 00:02:18.500
MAN:
Did you hear
about this new girl?

00:02:18.500 --> 00:02:20.300
MAN 2:
Yeah, she's supposed
to be from the Kuchiki clan.

00:02:20.300 --> 00:02:23.900
MAN 3:
Great, just what we need--
another captain's pet

00:02:23.900 --> 00:02:25.934
getting treated better
than the rest of us.

00:02:25.934 --> 00:02:27.800
MAN 4:
I heard she didn't even
have to pass the graduation

00:02:27.800 --> 00:02:29.633
exam to get into the squad.

00:02:29.633 --> 00:02:30.867
MAN:
What a joke.

00:02:30.867 --> 00:02:33.567
And here we've got to
bust out butts just

00:02:33.567 --> 00:02:34.567
to stay out of trouble.

00:02:34.567 --> 00:02:36.033
MAN 2:
It's not fair,
but that's life.

00:02:36.033 --> 00:02:37.834
RUKIA:
It's the same here
as everywhere else.

00:02:37.834 --> 00:02:39.166
KAIEN:
Hey!

00:02:39.166 --> 00:02:41.333
What are you lazy bums
doing hanging around here?

00:02:41.333 --> 00:02:44.333
Get back to your posts,
all of you.

00:02:46.967 --> 00:02:50.700
Hello, I'm Lieutenant
Kaien Shiba. Welcome aboard.

00:02:53.734 --> 00:02:54.867
I see.

00:02:54.867 --> 00:02:55.867
Yes, sir.

00:02:55.867 --> 00:02:59.266
What did you just say?

00:02:59.266 --> 00:03:01.867
What kind of greeting
is that supposed to be?

00:03:01.867 --> 00:03:04.700
I am your commanding officer.

00:03:04.700 --> 00:03:06.100
You are supposed
to state your name and say,

00:03:06.100 --> 00:03:07.934
pleased to meet you sir.

00:03:07.934 --> 00:03:09.633
What's your name, damn it?

00:03:10.400 --> 00:03:13.767
Uh, it's Rukia Kuchiki, sir.

00:03:13.767 --> 00:03:16.033
Hm? And?

00:03:16.033 --> 00:03:18.400
And-- and I'm pleased
to meet your, sir!

00:03:18.400 --> 00:03:19.900
All right.

00:03:19.900 --> 00:03:22.166
You're okay, Rukia.

00:03:22.166 --> 00:03:23.734
RUKIA:
A normal greeting.

00:03:23.734 --> 00:03:25.200
A normal scolding.

00:03:25.200 --> 00:03:29.166
A normal relationship between
officer and subordinate.

00:03:29.166 --> 00:03:31.367
Welcome to Squad 13, the
best squad of them all.

00:03:31.367 --> 00:03:35.066
Unfortunately, our captain
isn't in the best of health.

00:03:35.066 --> 00:03:37.233
So I pretty much run
things around here.

00:03:37.233 --> 00:03:39.166
In fact, it's not
a problem if now and then you

00:03:39.166 --> 00:03:42.834
forgot and accidentally
addressed me as Captain Kaien.

00:03:42.834 --> 00:03:47.166
Okay, I'll try to remember.

00:03:47.166 --> 00:03:49.834
RUKIA:
After such a long,
strange road,

00:03:49.834 --> 00:03:53.467
that sense of normalcy
was exactly what I wanted.

00:03:53.467 --> 00:03:58.300
RUKIA:
Lord Byakuya, my entrance to
Squad 13 today was successful.

00:04:00.667 --> 00:04:02.767
What seat where you named?

00:04:02.767 --> 00:04:07.567
Uh, well, my deepest
apologies, brother.

00:04:07.567 --> 00:04:10.500
But with my abilities,
I wasn't able to qualify

00:04:10.500 --> 00:04:12.400
for an officer seed upon entry.

00:04:12.400 --> 00:04:15.300
I see.

00:04:15.300 --> 00:04:16.900
You may go.

00:04:21.266 --> 00:04:24.767
Ah, not the long face again. Now
what?

00:04:24.767 --> 00:04:25.767
[GASPS]

00:04:25.767 --> 00:04:27.533
And why is it you
practically jump out

00:04:27.533 --> 00:04:29.734
of your skin every
time you see me?

00:04:29.734 --> 00:04:32.166
You're hurting
my feelings.

00:04:32.166 --> 00:04:33.633
Anyway, I brought this for you.

00:04:33.633 --> 00:04:35.066
So drink up.

00:04:35.066 --> 00:04:36.500
Oh.

00:04:40.433 --> 00:04:43.567
KAIEN:
Knowing you, you probably
won't tell me anything.

00:04:43.567 --> 00:04:45.133
But I have to ask.

00:04:45.133 --> 00:04:47.233
What's got you so depressed?

00:04:47.233 --> 00:04:48.800
Oh.

00:04:48.800 --> 00:04:50.300
Just remember this.

00:04:50.300 --> 00:04:52.834
As long as you're a part
of this squad, Rukia,

00:04:52.834 --> 00:04:56.667
I will stand by you even
if it costs me my life.

00:04:56.667 --> 00:04:58.400
Lieutenant--

00:04:58.400 --> 00:05:00.367
Ah, yeah!
Smells like love.

00:05:00.367 --> 00:05:02.033
Oh, you're so cool,
Lieutenant.

00:05:02.033 --> 00:05:04.000
I just love
a man in uniform.

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:04.967
Did you hear that?

00:05:04.967 --> 00:05:06.333
I'll stand by you?

00:05:06.333 --> 00:05:08.667
You've got him wrapped
around your little finger--

00:05:08.667 --> 00:05:10.333
Kiyone, Sentaro,
shut up, you two!

00:05:10.333 --> 00:05:12.000
How dare you show up
for duty drunk again?

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:13.834
[SLURRING]:
Don't let it get to you,
Rukia.

00:05:13.834 --> 00:05:16.000
I'm from the slums too,
so I know what it's like.

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:17.166
All of these snobs telling me

00:05:17.166 --> 00:05:19.867
I'm low class really
gets annoying.

00:05:19.867 --> 00:05:23.433
Whenever they try, just do like
I do and flick a booger at 'em.

00:05:23.433 --> 00:05:24.633
Works every time.

00:05:24.633 --> 00:05:26.867
Now that's class!

00:05:26.867 --> 00:05:28.367
SENTARO:
Right!

00:05:28.367 --> 00:05:31.133
All right! That's enough out
of you two loudmouths.

00:05:31.133 --> 00:05:33.867
Sober up and get
back to your post!

00:05:33.867 --> 00:05:35.000
[SPUTTERING]

00:05:35.000 --> 00:05:38.500
We were just having fun.
You're such a killjoy!

00:05:38.500 --> 00:05:39.834
[LAUGHING]

00:05:39.834 --> 00:05:42.967
[ARGUING]

00:05:42.967 --> 00:05:46.700
Kaien always had a way
of making me feel at ease.

00:05:46.700 --> 00:05:47.900
KAIEN:
...file a report!

00:05:47.900 --> 00:05:51.367
[ROARS]

00:05:51.367 --> 00:05:52.934
Die, Hollow!

00:05:57.700 --> 00:05:58.700
Well done, Lieutenant!

00:05:58.700 --> 00:06:00.433
Excellent!
Make quick work of that.

00:06:00.433 --> 00:06:02.934
Just like you always do!

00:06:02.934 --> 00:06:05.333
KAIEN:
All right.
Mission accomplished!

00:06:05.333 --> 00:06:07.967
[CHATTERING]

00:06:09.867 --> 00:06:13.767
I hurt myself.

00:06:13.767 --> 00:06:16.333
Huh?

00:06:16.333 --> 00:06:17.567
Ms. Miyako.

00:06:17.567 --> 00:06:19.266
Are you all right?

00:06:19.266 --> 00:06:20.300
[NERVOUSLY]:
Oh, yes.

00:06:20.300 --> 00:06:22.533
Yes, it was nothing.
Thank you.

00:06:22.533 --> 00:06:24.200
Oh, good.
I was worried for a second.

00:06:24.200 --> 00:06:26.800
KAIEN:
Hey! Who's that?

00:06:26.800 --> 00:06:30.500
Is that you, Miyako?

00:06:30.500 --> 00:06:32.967
I wasn't expecting you.
How long have you been here?

00:06:32.967 --> 00:06:34.400
Oh, I've been here
a little while--

00:06:34.400 --> 00:06:36.700
long enough to see you
take care of the Hollow.

00:06:36.700 --> 00:06:39.166
I just came in
case you messed it up

00:06:39.166 --> 00:06:40.500
and needed me to save you.

00:06:40.500 --> 00:06:44.567
[LAUGHS]
Well, at least it's nice
to know you have my back.

00:06:44.567 --> 00:06:45.600
[LAUGHS]

00:06:45.600 --> 00:06:47.233
Rukia, go alert the squad.

00:06:47.233 --> 00:06:49.500
Have Sentaro and Kiyone help.

00:06:49.500 --> 00:06:51.233
Tell them that
we're pulling out.

00:06:51.233 --> 00:06:52.767
Yes, sir.

00:06:52.767 --> 00:06:55.400
And thank you for
helping me, Ms. Miyako.

00:06:55.400 --> 00:06:58.467
[LAUGHS]
You take care of yourself now.

00:06:58.467 --> 00:07:00.266
Yes, I will.

00:07:04.967 --> 00:07:08.166
RUKIA:
Miyako was
Captain Kaien's wife.

00:07:08.166 --> 00:07:11.133
She had risen quickly to
the rank of third seed officer

00:07:11.133 --> 00:07:12.467
in the squad.

00:07:12.467 --> 00:07:14.934
Not only was she
a strong warrior,

00:07:14.934 --> 00:07:18.066
she was intelligent,
kind, and beautiful.

00:07:21.800 --> 00:07:23.567
She was my idol.

00:07:23.567 --> 00:07:25.233
I admired her so much.

00:07:25.233 --> 00:07:28.133
I hoped some day I
could be like her.

00:07:29.600 --> 00:07:32.567
Then one day,
Miyako received orders

00:07:32.567 --> 00:07:35.300
to lead a
reconnaissance mission.

00:07:35.300 --> 00:07:38.266
Unfortunately, this Hollow
is an unknown entity.

00:07:38.266 --> 00:07:40.500
And none of the Soul
Reapers it's attacked

00:07:40.500 --> 00:07:43.867
have survived to report back.

00:07:43.867 --> 00:07:45.767
Don't be reckless.

00:07:45.767 --> 00:07:48.333
You'd have to admit, that's some
pretty unusual advice

00:07:48.333 --> 00:07:49.700
coming from someone
like you, Lieutenant.

00:07:49.700 --> 00:07:51.333
[LAUGHS]

00:07:51.333 --> 00:07:53.433
KAIEN:
Quit joking around.

00:07:56.400 --> 00:07:57.967
It's all right.

00:07:57.967 --> 00:08:01.200
I take my mission
as a Soul Reaper very seriously.

00:08:01.200 --> 00:08:03.000
And this Hollow's
horrible crimes

00:08:03.000 --> 00:08:04.867
cannot be allowed
to continue.

00:08:04.867 --> 00:08:08.200
I'll do whatever I can to
put a stop to such evil.

00:08:08.200 --> 00:08:09.834
Ms. Miyako.

00:08:09.834 --> 00:08:11.200
Oh, don't worry about me.

00:08:11.200 --> 00:08:13.867
This is just a recon mission.

00:08:13.867 --> 00:08:16.133
We'll gather all the information
and leave all the heavy stuff

00:08:16.133 --> 00:08:17.533
to you and the Lieutenant.

00:08:17.533 --> 00:08:19.600
Recon team, let's move out.

00:08:19.600 --> 00:08:21.000
[TOGETHER]:
Right.

00:08:27.700 --> 00:08:30.600
[COUGHING]

00:08:30.600 --> 00:08:32.133
Do you need anything,
Captain?

00:08:32.133 --> 00:08:34.667
No, thanks.
I'll be fine.

00:08:34.667 --> 00:08:36.200
RUKIA:
Excuse me.

00:08:39.767 --> 00:08:44.100
Rukia, is there any report yet
from the reconnaissance team?

00:08:44.100 --> 00:08:47.200
I'm afraid not, sir.
They still haven't returned.

00:08:47.200 --> 00:08:48.734
[FOOTSTEPS]

00:08:48.734 --> 00:08:51.800
Sir, the recon team--
there's bad news!

00:08:51.800 --> 00:08:53.500
[ALL GASP]

00:08:55.734 --> 00:08:57.233
[GASPS]

00:08:57.233 --> 00:08:59.033
Miyako!

00:08:59.033 --> 00:09:03.600
She's unconscious now, but
her life isn't in any danger.

00:09:03.600 --> 00:09:05.100
And the others?

00:09:05.100 --> 00:09:06.266
The others
are all dead, sir.

00:09:06.266 --> 00:09:08.200
All four of them?

00:09:11.133 --> 00:09:13.033
RUKIA:
Kaien.

00:09:28.166 --> 00:09:30.133
We've had our share
of bad luck lately.

00:09:30.133 --> 00:09:32.133
Yeah, I can't believe
the whole reconnaissance

00:09:32.133 --> 00:09:33.734
team got wiped
out like that.

00:09:33.734 --> 00:09:36.066
Except for Ms. Miyako,
that is.

00:09:36.066 --> 00:09:38.066
MAN:
How is she?
Is she gonna be all right?

00:09:38.066 --> 00:09:39.967
MAN 2:
Yeah, they said
her life's not in danger.

00:09:39.967 --> 00:09:41.400
MAN:
Well, that's good.

00:09:41.400 --> 00:09:43.800
She's one person the squad
really couldn't do without.

00:09:43.800 --> 00:09:46.033
MAN 2:
Yeah.

00:09:46.033 --> 00:09:49.600
Huh? Ms. Miyako, should you
be out of bed so soon?

00:09:49.600 --> 00:09:54.734
[SHOUTING]

00:09:54.734 --> 00:09:55.834
MAN:
Miyako! Agh!

00:09:55.834 --> 00:09:57.633
[SHOUTS]

00:10:03.000 --> 00:10:04.066
What's going on?

00:10:08.467 --> 00:10:10.934
[LAUGHS]

00:10:10.934 --> 00:10:12.667
Ms. Miyako?

00:10:12.667 --> 00:10:14.233
SENTARO:
What happened here?

00:10:14.233 --> 00:10:15.300
This is horrible!

00:10:22.100 --> 00:10:23.600
Stop it, Miyako!

00:10:24.567 --> 00:10:27.533
[GASPING]

00:10:36.700 --> 00:10:38.433
[MAN GROANS]

00:10:38.433 --> 00:10:40.033
[SHOUTING]

00:10:40.033 --> 00:10:41.100
Kaien, hurry.

00:10:46.800 --> 00:10:49.633
I can't believe
she did this.

00:10:49.633 --> 00:10:51.133
RUKIA:
Oh, Kaien.

00:10:51.133 --> 00:10:53.300
KAIEN:
Let me go after her,
Captain.

00:10:53.300 --> 00:10:55.767
She couldn't have
gotten very far, sir.

00:10:55.767 --> 00:10:56.767
No, don't.

00:10:56.767 --> 00:10:59.367
Think about it, Kaien.

00:10:59.367 --> 00:11:02.967
Following her is exactly what
the enemy wants you to do.

00:11:02.967 --> 00:11:04.033
KAIEN:
That may be.

00:11:04.033 --> 00:11:06.266
But it's still
the only option.

00:11:06.266 --> 00:11:08.834
This monster that's
controlling Miyako

00:11:08.834 --> 00:11:12.800
used her to kill her own
men, men who trusted her.

00:11:12.800 --> 00:11:16.333
Miyako's honor has been defiled.

00:11:16.333 --> 00:11:18.467
You must let me go, Captain.

00:11:22.533 --> 00:11:24.600
UKITAKE:
Very well.

00:11:24.600 --> 00:11:25.867
I shall go with you.

00:11:25.867 --> 00:11:26.867
[GASPING]

00:11:26.867 --> 00:11:29.200
You, Captain?

00:11:29.200 --> 00:11:30.934
Mm.

00:11:31.633 --> 00:11:33.367
You come too, Rukia.

00:11:33.367 --> 00:11:34.367
Yes, sir.

00:11:34.367 --> 00:11:36.000
You two-- seal off this area

00:11:36.000 --> 00:11:38.533
and call the squad
to battle stations.

00:11:38.533 --> 00:11:39.533
[TOGETHER]
Understood, sir.

00:11:39.533 --> 00:11:41.467
SENTARO:
Let's go!

00:11:44.000 --> 00:11:46.400
HOLLOW:
I smell more prey
approaching--

00:11:46.400 --> 00:11:49.066
more foolish meat.

00:12:06.300 --> 00:12:07.367
RUKIA:
What is that?

00:12:07.367 --> 00:12:08.734
UKITAKE:
Kaien.

00:12:13.633 --> 00:12:14.700
Huh?

00:12:30.633 --> 00:12:32.767
I'll go first, sir.

00:12:32.767 --> 00:12:35.600
I'll scout out what
its abilities are.

00:12:35.600 --> 00:12:36.734
Huh?

00:12:36.734 --> 00:12:40.200
KAIEN:
Captain, I beg of you.

00:12:40.200 --> 00:12:42.200
Permission to go fight it alone.

00:12:47.700 --> 00:12:49.333
Go.

00:12:53.367 --> 00:12:57.333
[LAUGHS]
So you're the first, eh?

00:12:57.333 --> 00:12:58.567
You're nothing but a boy.

00:13:02.033 --> 00:13:06.667
KAIEN:
Tell me,
how many Soul Reapers

00:13:06.667 --> 00:13:08.266
have you devoured so far?

00:13:08.266 --> 00:13:10.333
Uh, how many?

00:13:10.333 --> 00:13:12.900
[LAUGHS]
Sorry, boy.

00:13:12.900 --> 00:13:16.166
I don't keep track
of such trivial things.

00:13:16.166 --> 00:13:20.033
Have you ever, even once,
had any regrets about it?

00:13:20.033 --> 00:13:22.200
That's such a stupid question.

00:13:22.200 --> 00:13:25.667
I have a heart, you know,
just like you.

00:13:25.667 --> 00:13:28.200
There isn't a single night
that I don't have regrets

00:13:28.200 --> 00:13:30.266
after eating a Soul Reaper.

00:13:30.266 --> 00:13:34.834
Even now I'm having regrets
about that woman Soul Reaper.

00:13:34.834 --> 00:13:36.633
I regret not eating
the rest of her!

00:13:36.633 --> 00:13:39.066
[LAUGHS]

00:13:39.066 --> 00:13:42.567
So you controlled her
and made her kill her comrades?

00:13:42.567 --> 00:13:45.166
Controlled her?
[LAUGHS]

00:13:45.166 --> 00:13:47.367
Oh, not the way
you're imagining.

00:13:47.367 --> 00:13:51.667
I was actually inside her body,
then I ate my way out of her

00:13:51.667 --> 00:13:54.000
and returned
to the form you see now.

00:13:54.000 --> 00:13:56.734
Too bad you didn't
get to see that part.

00:13:56.734 --> 00:14:01.367
[LAUGHS]

00:14:01.367 --> 00:14:03.700
Want to see what
it's like for yourself?

00:14:03.700 --> 00:14:05.567
Come on, boy.
I'll eat you too!

00:14:07.567 --> 00:14:11.300
[GROANS]

00:14:11.300 --> 00:14:14.667
You're fast,
but not fast enough.

00:14:14.667 --> 00:14:17.500
Rankle the seas and the skies,
Nejibana!

00:14:22.200 --> 00:14:23.166
What the hell?

00:14:23.166 --> 00:14:24.900
You fell for it, boy.

00:14:24.900 --> 00:14:27.867
Once every night,
the first one to touch tentacles

00:14:27.867 --> 00:14:31.367
will see his
Zanpakuto destroyed!

00:14:31.367 --> 00:14:32.600
[SHOUTS]

00:14:32.600 --> 00:14:35.667
Impossible. I've never
heard of such a power.

00:14:35.667 --> 00:14:37.667
Kaien, get away!

00:14:39.700 --> 00:14:42.700
Captain, Kaien
has been disarmed.

00:14:42.700 --> 00:14:43.800
We have to help him.

00:14:43.800 --> 00:14:46.000
But if we were to
step in now, what

00:14:46.000 --> 00:14:49.066
would become of Kaien's pride.

00:14:49.066 --> 00:14:51.367
Even if by going to
his aid you are somehow

00:14:51.367 --> 00:14:55.166
successful in saving his
life, the cost of such an act

00:14:55.166 --> 00:14:59.133
would certainly be the death
of his pride forever.

00:14:59.133 --> 00:15:01.266
That doesn't make any
sense at all, Captain.

00:15:01.266 --> 00:15:04.700
What good is pride
to a man if he's dead.

00:15:04.700 --> 00:15:08.633
Listen now,
and remember these words.

00:15:08.633 --> 00:15:10.367
There are two kinds of battles.

00:15:10.367 --> 00:15:12.233
And those of us who have
chosen to be warriors

00:15:12.233 --> 00:15:15.033
and to fight those
battles must always

00:15:15.033 --> 00:15:19.066
be aware of the difference
between the two.

00:15:19.066 --> 00:15:21.467
There are battles that are
fought to protect lives,

00:15:21.467 --> 00:15:24.333
and there are battles that
are fought to defend honor.

00:15:26.967 --> 00:15:29.800
Right now, Kaien is fighting
with all his heart and soul

00:15:29.800 --> 00:15:32.533
to defend honor--
that of his men who died,

00:15:32.533 --> 00:15:34.900
and his own honor,

00:15:34.900 --> 00:15:39.500
and above all,
his beloved wife's honor.

00:15:44.166 --> 00:15:48.133
[GROWLING]

00:15:48.133 --> 00:15:51.100
[LAUGHS]

00:15:51.100 --> 00:15:53.200
What's the matter Soul Reaper?

00:15:53.200 --> 00:15:57.567
Too full of yourself to ask
your friends to help you?

00:15:57.567 --> 00:15:59.033
Shut up.

00:15:59.033 --> 00:16:02.367
I don't need a sword or anything
else to handle scum like you.

00:16:02.367 --> 00:16:03.934
We'll see about that.

00:16:03.934 --> 00:16:06.233
Because now I'm
going to do unto you

00:16:06.233 --> 00:16:09.934
just as I did unto your
beloved and delicious wife.

00:16:09.934 --> 00:16:13.467
I'm going to play you like
a puppet from the inside.

00:16:13.467 --> 00:16:16.734
And against your will,
you'll slay your comrades

00:16:16.734 --> 00:16:18.533
with your own hand.

00:16:18.533 --> 00:16:22.934
[LAUGHS]

00:16:38.867 --> 00:16:42.166
Lieutenant Kaien?

00:16:42.166 --> 00:16:45.667
HOLLOW:
Yes, what is it, girl?

00:16:45.667 --> 00:16:47.233
What do you want?

00:16:47.233 --> 00:16:48.266
[GASPS]

00:16:48.266 --> 00:16:50.200
[SLURPS]

00:16:50.200 --> 00:16:53.166
Lieutenant Kaien?

00:16:53.166 --> 00:16:54.834
HOLLOW:
What is with you, girl?

00:16:54.834 --> 00:16:57.967
Why do you keep repeating
my name again and again?

00:16:57.967 --> 00:17:00.467
Are you that worried about me?

00:17:00.467 --> 00:17:03.567
Or maybe you're in love with me!

00:17:03.567 --> 00:17:04.967
[GASPS]

00:17:04.967 --> 00:17:08.567
[LAUGHS]
I guess if you really
love me that much,

00:17:08.567 --> 00:17:10.800
then maybe I should
eat you first!

00:17:15.567 --> 00:17:16.567
Captain.

00:17:16.567 --> 00:17:17.800
UKITAKE:
Rukia, get out of here.

00:17:17.800 --> 00:17:18.934
Huh?

00:17:18.934 --> 00:17:19.900
Get out of here!

00:17:19.900 --> 00:17:21.333
Run away, now!

00:17:23.700 --> 00:17:27.467
Why, why did this
have to happen?

00:17:27.467 --> 00:17:29.166
[SOBBING]

00:17:29.166 --> 00:17:31.500
Kaien!

00:17:33.800 --> 00:17:36.000
HOLLOW:
Why I you attacking me,
Soul Reaper?

00:17:36.000 --> 00:17:38.800
I think I know what
you're waiting for.

00:17:38.800 --> 00:17:41.233
You're trying to think of a way
to rip me out of this body,

00:17:41.233 --> 00:17:43.567
so you can still
save your friend.

00:17:43.567 --> 00:17:45.166
Isn't that right?

00:17:45.166 --> 00:17:48.000
But this is different
from human possession.

00:17:48.000 --> 00:17:51.734
We are both spirit beings,
and now our spirits are united.

00:17:51.734 --> 00:17:53.867
It can never be undone.

00:17:53.867 --> 00:17:55.533
[HOLLOW GROANS]

00:17:55.533 --> 00:17:58.100
UKITAKE:
I see.
Then you leave me no choice.

00:17:58.100 --> 00:18:01.767
I'll kill his body
and you inside it.

00:18:01.767 --> 00:18:04.867
HOLLOW:
Are you insane?

00:18:04.867 --> 00:18:08.333
What kind of a Soul Reaper
would slay one of his own men?

00:18:08.333 --> 00:18:10.300
Kaien no longer exists.

00:18:10.300 --> 00:18:14.166
I won't let his body become food
for a monster like you.

00:18:14.166 --> 00:18:15.266
Now die!

00:18:18.200 --> 00:18:21.667
Coward!

00:18:21.667 --> 00:18:25.600
[COUGHING]

00:18:28.333 --> 00:18:30.734
UKITAKE:
Now, of all times.

00:18:33.333 --> 00:18:34.567
UKITAKE:
Rukia!

00:18:34.567 --> 00:18:37.367
You were supposed to get
away from here, you idiot!

00:18:37.367 --> 00:18:40.200
RUKIA:
I don't know
what made me go back.

00:18:40.200 --> 00:18:41.867
I didn't have a plan.

00:18:41.867 --> 00:18:43.066
[HOLLOW LAUGHING]

00:18:50.500 --> 00:18:51.767
Rukia!

00:18:54.200 --> 00:18:57.100
[HOLLOW GROWLS]

00:19:11.333 --> 00:19:12.834
KAIEN:
My captain--

00:19:12.834 --> 00:19:13.900
[GASPS]

00:19:13.900 --> 00:19:16.133
KAIEN:
--thank you
for understanding

00:19:16.133 --> 00:19:21.400
and for letting me
fight to the end.

00:19:21.400 --> 00:19:24.133
RUKIA:
But Kaien, does that mean you--

00:19:24.133 --> 00:19:28.734
KAIEN:
Rukia, I apologize to you
for getting you involved

00:19:28.734 --> 00:19:31.934
in all of this in
the first place.

00:19:31.934 --> 00:19:34.867
I know this was painful.

00:19:34.867 --> 00:19:38.533
But thanks to you, I'm saved.

00:19:38.533 --> 00:19:42.433
Now I can still
leave my heart here.

00:19:44.734 --> 00:19:49.800
RUKIA:
No, I haven't done anything
deserving of anyone's thanks.

00:19:49.800 --> 00:19:51.667
I ran away because
I was afraid to fight.

00:19:51.667 --> 00:19:55.233
[RUKIA SOBBING]

00:19:55.233 --> 00:19:57.133
Then I ran back.

00:19:57.133 --> 00:19:59.467
But it was only
because I couldn't

00:19:59.467 --> 00:20:01.500
stand to see you suffer.

00:20:03.567 --> 00:20:08.266
The only one I saved
was myself.

00:20:08.266 --> 00:20:11.667
I'm not worth
shedding blood over.

00:20:11.667 --> 00:20:13.233
Not ever.

00:20:18.200 --> 00:20:20.400
UKITAKE: Byakuya!
[FOOTSTEPS]

00:20:22.300 --> 00:20:25.033
The execution--
it's been moved!

00:20:25.033 --> 00:20:26.400
Yes, to tomorrow.

00:20:26.400 --> 00:20:28.667
Well, what are you
going to do about it?

00:20:28.667 --> 00:20:30.667
Why should I do
anything about it?

00:20:30.667 --> 00:20:32.900
Huh?
Are you serious?

00:20:32.900 --> 00:20:34.433
The date has been set.

00:20:34.433 --> 00:20:36.867
If that is the decision
and the order,

00:20:36.867 --> 00:20:39.333
then there is nothing
to do but to head it.

00:20:39.333 --> 00:20:42.800
Don't bother me again
with such petty matters.

00:20:42.800 --> 00:20:43.867
Excuse me.

00:20:43.867 --> 00:20:45.567
Well, wait just a minute!

00:20:45.567 --> 00:20:47.467
This is not some stranger.

00:20:47.467 --> 00:20:49.834
Your sister's life
is at stake here.

00:20:49.834 --> 00:20:53.100
If someone doesn't do something,
she's likely to die!

00:20:53.100 --> 00:20:56.200
[COUGHING]

00:20:56.200 --> 00:20:57.500
You should be careful.

00:20:57.500 --> 00:21:00.266
You'll only shorten
your life, Ukitake.

00:21:00.266 --> 00:21:02.500
Having already lost
your lieutenant,

00:21:02.500 --> 00:21:05.166
I wouldn't think losing
one more would matter.

00:21:11.100 --> 00:21:14.300
In any case,
Rukia is a member of my house.

00:21:14.300 --> 00:21:16.533
As such,
whether she lives or dies

00:21:16.533 --> 00:21:19.667
is none of your business.

00:21:19.667 --> 00:21:23.533
I trust you'll refrain from
taking any reckless action.

00:21:26.000 --> 00:21:27.934
[♪♪♪]

00:21:27.934 --> 00:21:29.767
♪ Happypeople ♪

00:21:29.767 --> 00:21:32.400
♪ Come on, come on
Come on ♪

00:21:32.400 --> 00:21:34.700
♪ Happypeople ♪

00:21:34.700 --> 00:21:36.100
♪ Here we go ♪

00:21:36.100 --> 00:21:39.266
♪ Everybody stand up ♪

00:21:39.266 --> 00:21:42.734
[SINGING IN JAPANESE]

00:21:47.934 --> 00:21:52.300
♪ Keep your head right up ♪

00:21:52.300 --> 00:21:53.600
♪ To the sky ♪

00:21:53.600 --> 00:21:54.834
[SINGING IN JAPANESE]

00:21:54.834 --> 00:21:55.934
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

00:21:55.934 --> 00:21:57.100
[SINGING IN JAPANESE]

00:21:57.100 --> 00:21:59.200
♪ Oh, yeah ♪
♪ Just call me any time ♪

00:21:59.200 --> 00:22:00.300
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

00:22:00.300 --> 00:22:02.533
[SINGING IN JAPANESE]

00:22:02.533 --> 00:22:06.867
♪ Happypeople's in the house ♪

00:22:06.867 --> 00:22:10.200
[SINGING IN JAPANESE]

00:22:11.200 --> 00:22:15.500
♪ Happypeople's in the house ♪

00:22:15.500 --> 00:22:18.734
[SINGING IN JAPANESE]

00:22:18.734 --> 00:22:19.934
♪ Well... ♪

00:22:19.934 --> 00:22:22.567
♪ Happypeople ♪
♪ In the house ♪

00:22:23.433 --> 00:22:24.767
♪ All right ♪

00:22:24.767 --> 00:22:26.166
♪ Happypeople ♪

00:22:26.166 --> 00:22:28.867
♪ Mmm, happy ♪

00:22:30.900 --> 00:22:33.233
SENTARO:
I'm so devoted
to Captain Ukitake,

00:22:33.233 --> 00:22:34.333
I'd follow him anywhere!

00:22:34.333 --> 00:22:35.600
KIYONE:
Give it up, Sentaro!

00:22:35.600 --> 00:22:37.734
I'm way more devoted
to the captain than you!

00:22:37.734 --> 00:22:40.233
SENTARO:
Oh yeah? Well--
well I stalk the captain 24/7.

00:22:40.233 --> 00:22:41.500
KIYONE:
Well, I check his schedule

00:22:41.500 --> 00:22:43.867
and get where
he's going even before he does.

00:22:43.867 --> 00:22:46.066
SENTARO:
Wait a minute.
Is that even legal?

